706708f-a.text:
(1)
Sheepshead Bay Road, at the S.E. corner of East 14th Street, showing the St. Mark's R.C. Church, which was organised in 1868. This edifice was demolished by fire on February 24, 1929.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showimg a later view
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

706707f-a.text:
Sheepshead Bay Road, south side, from and including East 14th Street, to, but not including Ave., "Y". All the houses seen are frame; the house on the corner has a brick font. (Sheepshead Bay Road, is arbitrarily set to run east and west from East 13th Street, to Jerome Ave).
July 9, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
